153 enum ActionButtonType
154 {
155  ACTION_BUTTON_SPELL = 0x00,
156  ACTION_BUTTON_C = 0x01, // click?
157  ACTION_BUTTON_EQSET = 0x20,
158  ACTION_BUTTON_MACRO = 0x40,
159  ACTION_BUTTON_CMACRO = ACTION_BUTTON_C | ACTION_BUTTON_MACRO,
160  ACTION_BUTTON_ITEM = 0x80
161 };
162 
163 #define ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(X) (uint32(X) & 0x00FFFFFF)
164 #define ACTION_BUTTON_TYPE(X) ((uint32(X) & 0xFF000000) >> 24)
165 #define MAX_ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION_VALUE (0x00FFFFFF+1)
166 
167 struct ActionButton
168 {
169  ActionButton() : packedData(0), uState(ACTIONBUTTON_NEW) {}
170 
171  uint32 packedData;
172  ActionButtonUpdateState uState;
173 
174  // helpers
175  ActionButtonType GetType() const { return ActionButtonType(ACTION_BUTTON_TYPE(packedData)); }
176  uint32 GetAction() const { return ACTION_BUTTON_ACTION(packedData); }
177  void SetActionAndType(uint32 action, ActionButtonType type)
178  {
179  uint32 newData = action | (uint32(type) << 24);
180  if (newData != packedData || uState == ACTIONBUTTON_DELETED)
181  {
182  packedData = newData;
183  if (uState != ACTIONBUTTON_NEW)
184  uState = ACTIONBUTTON_CHANGED;
185  }
186  }
187 };
188

199 enum GlyphUpdateState
200 {
201  GLYPH_UNCHANGED = 0,
202  GLYPH_CHANGED = 1,
203  GLYPH_NEW = 2,
204  GLYPH_DELETED = 3
205 };
206 
207 struct Glyph
208 {
209  uint32 id;
210  GlyphUpdateState uState;
211 
212  Glyph() : id(0), uState(GLYPH_UNCHANGED) { }
213 
214  uint32 GetId() const { return id; }
215 
216  void SetId(uint32 newId)
217  {
218  if (newId == id)
219  return;
220 
221  if (id == 0 && uState == GLYPH_UNCHANGED) // not exist yet in db and already saved
222  {
223  uState = GLYPH_NEW;
224  }
225  else if (newId == 0)
226  {
227  if (uState == GLYPH_NEW) // delete before add new -> no change
228  uState = GLYPH_UNCHANGED;
229  else // delete existing data
230  uState = GLYPH_DELETED;
231  }
232  else if (uState != GLYPH_NEW) // if not new data, change current data
233  {
234  uState = GLYPH_CHANGED;
235  }
236 
237  id = newId;
238  }
239 };

370 struct Runes
371 {
372  RuneInfo runes[MAX_RUNES];
373  uint8 runeState; // mask of available runes
374 
375  void SetRuneState(uint8 index, bool set = true)
376  {
377  if (set)
378  runeState |= (1 << index); // usable
379  else
380  runeState &= ~(1 << index); // on cooldown
381  }
382 };

478 class MirrorTimer
479 {
480  public:
481  enum Type
482  {
483  FATIGUE = 0,
484  BREATH = 1,
485  FEIGNDEATH = 2,
486 
487  NUM_CLIENT_TIMERS,
488 
489  ENVIRONMENTAL = NUM_CLIENT_TIMERS,
490 
491  NUM_TIMERS
492  };
493 
494  enum Status
495  {
496  UNCHANGED = 0,
497  FULL_UPDATE = 1,
498  STATUS_UPDATE = 2,
499  };
500 
501  MirrorTimer(Type type) : m_type(type), m_scale(-1), m_spellId(0), m_status(UNCHANGED), m_active(false), m_frozen(false) {}
502 
503  inline bool IsActive() const { return m_active; }
504  inline bool IsRegenerating() const { return (m_scale > 0); }
505  inline bool IsFrozen() const { return (m_frozen && !IsRegenerating()); }
506 
507  inline Type GetType() const { return m_type; }
508  inline uint32 GetRemaining() const { return (m_tracker.GetInterval() - m_tracker.GetCurrent()); }
509  inline uint32 GetDuration() const { return m_tracker.GetInterval(); }
510  inline int32 GetScale() const { return m_scale; }
511  inline uint32 GetSpellId() const { return m_spellId; }
512 
513  inline Status FetchStatus();
514 
515  inline void Stop();
516 
517  inline void Start(uint32 interval, uint32 spellId = 0);
518  inline void Start(uint32 current, uint32 max, uint32 spellId);
519 
520  inline void SetRemaining(uint32 duration);
521  inline void SetDuration(uint32 duration);
522 
523  inline void SetFrozen(bool state);
524 
525  inline void SetScale(int32 scale);
526 
527  bool Update(uint32 diff);
528 
529  private:
530  Type m_type;
531  int32 m_scale;
532  uint32 m_spellId;
533 
534  ShortIntervalTimer m_tracker;
535  ShortIntervalTimer m_pulse;
536 
537  Status m_status;
538 
539  bool m_active;
540  bool m_frozen;
541 };

888 struct InstancePlayerBind
889 {
890  DungeonPersistentState* state;
891  bool perm;
892  /* permanent PlayerInstanceBinds are created in Raid/Heroic instances for players
893  that aren't already permanently bound when they are inside when a boss is killed
894  or when they enter an instance that the group leader is permanently bound to. */
895  /* extend state listing:
896  EXPIRED - doesn't affect anything unless manually re-extended by player
897  NORMAL - standard state
898  EXTENDED - won't be promoted to EXPIRED at next reset period, will instead be promoted to NORMAL */
899  BindExtensionState extendState;
900  InstancePlayerBind() : state(nullptr), perm(false), extendState(EXTEND_STATE_NORMAL) {}
901 };

942 class PlayerTaxi
943 {
944  public:
945  PlayerTaxi();
946  ~PlayerTaxi() {}
947  // Nodes
948  void InitTaxiNodesForLevel(uint32 race, uint32 chrClass, uint32 level);
949  void LoadTaxiMask(const char* data);
950 
951  bool IsTaximaskNodeKnown(uint32 nodeidx) const
952  {
953  uint8 field = uint8((nodeidx - 1) / 32);
954  uint32 submask = 1 << ((nodeidx - 1) % 32);
955  return (m_taximask[field] & submask) == submask;
956  }
957  bool SetTaximaskNode(uint32 nodeidx)
958  {
959  uint8 field = uint8((nodeidx - 1) / 32);
960  uint32 submask = 1 << ((nodeidx - 1) % 32);
961  if ((m_taximask[field] & submask) != submask)
962  {
963  m_taximask[field] |= submask;
964  return true;
965  }
966  return false;
967  }
968  void AppendTaximaskTo(ByteBuffer& data, bool all);
969 
970  friend std::ostringstream& operator<<(std::ostringstream& ss, PlayerTaxi const& taxi);
971 
972  private:
973  TaxiMask m_taximask;
974 };
975 
976 std::ostringstream& operator<< (std::ostringstream& ss, PlayerTaxi const& taxi);

1154  void SetAuctionAccessMode(int state)
1155  {
1156  m_ExtraFlags &= ~(PLAYER_EXTRA_AUCTION_ENEMY | PLAYER_EXTRA_AUCTION_NEUTRAL);
1157 
1158  if (state < 0)
1159  m_ExtraFlags |= PLAYER_EXTRA_AUCTION_ENEMY;
1160  else if (state > 0)
1161  m_ExtraFlags |= PLAYER_EXTRA_AUCTION_NEUTRAL;
1162  }

1494  uint16 FindQuestSlot(uint32 quest_id) const;
1495  uint32 GetQuestSlotQuestId(uint16 slot) const { return GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_ID_OFFSET); }
1496  void SetQuestSlot(uint16 slot, uint32 quest_id, uint32 timer = 0)
1497  {
1498  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_ID_OFFSET, quest_id);
1499  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET, 0);
1500  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET, 0);
1501  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET + 1, 0);
1502  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_TIME_OFFSET, timer);
1503  }
1504  void SetQuestSlotCounter(uint16 slot, uint8 counter, uint16 count)
1505  {
1506  uint64 val = GetUInt64Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET);
1507  val &= ~((uint64)0xFFFF << (counter * 16));
1508  val |= ((uint64)count << (counter * 16));
1509  SetUInt64Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_COUNTS_OFFSET, val);
1510  }
1511  void SetQuestSlotState(uint16 slot, uint32 state) { SetFlag(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET, state); }
1512  void RemoveQuestSlotState(uint16 slot, uint32 state) { RemoveFlag(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_STATE_OFFSET, state); }
1513  void SetQuestSlotTimer(uint16 slot, uint32 timer) { SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + slot * MAX_QUEST_OFFSET + QUEST_TIME_OFFSET, timer); }
1514  void SwapQuestSlot(uint16 slot1, uint16 slot2)
1515  {
1516  for (int i = 0; i < MAX_QUEST_OFFSET; ++i)
1517  {
1518  uint32 temp1 = GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot1 + i);
1519  uint32 temp2 = GetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot2 + i);
1520 
1521  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot1 + i, temp2);
1522  SetUInt32Value(PLAYER_QUEST_LOG_1_1 + MAX_QUEST_OFFSET * slot2 + i, temp1);
1523  }
1524  }

1616  void ModifyMoney(int32 d)
1617  {
1618  if (d < 0)
1619  SetMoney(GetMoney() > uint32(-d) ? GetMoney() + d : 0);
1620  else
1621  SetMoney(GetMoney() < uint32(MAX_MONEY_AMOUNT - d) ? GetMoney() + d : MAX_MONEY_AMOUNT);
1622 
1623  // "At Gold Limit"
1624  if (GetMoney() >= MAX_MONEY_AMOUNT)
1625  SendEquipError(EQUIP_ERR_TOO_MUCH_GOLD, nullptr, nullptr);
1626  }

1632  }

2048  template<typename T>
2049  bool CheckForGroup(T functor) const
2050  {
2051  if (Group const* group = GetGroup())
2052  {
2053  for (GroupReference const* ref = group->GetFirstMember(); ref != nullptr; ref = ref->next())
2054  {
2055  Player const* member = ref->getSource();
2056  if (member && functor(member))
2057  return true;
2058  }
2059  }
2060  else
2061  {
2062  if (functor(this))
2063  return true;
2064  }
2065  return false;
2066  }

2200  void SetBattleGroundId(uint32 val, BattleGroundTypeId bgTypeId)
2201  {
2202  m_bgData.bgInstanceID = val;
2203  m_bgData.bgTypeID = bgTypeId;
2204  m_bgData.m_needSave = true;

2206  uint32 AddBattleGroundQueueId(BattleGroundQueueTypeId val)
2207  {
2208  for (int i = 0; i < PLAYER_MAX_BATTLEGROUND_QUEUES; ++i)
2209  {
2210  if (m_bgBattleGroundQueueID[i].bgQueueTypeId == BATTLEGROUND_QUEUE_NONE || m_bgBattleGroundQueueID[i].bgQueueTypeId == val)
2211  {
2212  m_bgBattleGroundQueueID[i].bgQueueTypeId = val;
2213  m_bgBattleGroundQueueID[i].invitedToInstance = 0;
2214  return i;
2215  }
2216  }
2217  return PLAYER_MAX_BATTLEGROUND_QUEUES;
2218  }

2223  return true;
2224  return false;
2225  }

2235  return;

2507  // A Player can either have a playerbotMgr (to manage its bots), or have playerbotAI (if it is a bot), or
2508  // neither. Code that enables bots must create the playerbotMgr and set it using SetPlayerbotMgr.

2541  template <typename F>
2542  void RemoveSomeCooldown(F check)
2543  {
2544  auto spellCDItr = m_cooldownMap.begin();
2545  while (spellCDItr != m_cooldownMap.end())
2546  {
2547  SpellEntry const* entry = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellCDItr->first);
2548  if (entry && check(*entry))
2549  {
2550  SendClearCooldown(spellCDItr->first, this);
2551  spellCDItr = m_cooldownMap.erase(spellCDItr);
2552  }
2553  else
2554  ++spellCDItr;
2555  }
2556  }

2952 // "the bodies of template functions must be made available in a header file"
2953 template <class T> void Player::ApplySpellMod(uint32 spellId, SpellModOp op, T& basevalue, bool finalUse)
2954 {
2955  SpellEntry const* spellInfo = sSpellTemplate.LookupEntry<SpellEntry>(spellId);
2956  if (!spellInfo || spellInfo->SpellFamilyName != GetSpellClass() || spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR_EX3_IGNORE_CASTER_MODIFIERS)) return; // client condition
2957  int32 totalpct = 100;
2958  int32 totalflat = 0;
2959  std::vector<SpellModifier*> consumedFiniteMods;
2960  for (SpellModifier* mod : m_spellMods[op])
2961  {
2962  if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_CASTING_TIME || mod->op == SPELLMOD_COST)
2963  if (T((basevalue + totalflat) * std::max(0, totalpct) / 100) <= 0)
2964  break;
2965 
2966  if (!IsAffectedBySpellmod(spellInfo, mod, m_consumedMods))
2967  continue;
2968  if (mod->type == SPELLMOD_FLAT)
2969  totalflat += mod->value;
2970  else if (mod->type == SPELLMOD_PCT)
2971  {
2972  // special case (skip >10sec spell casts for instant cast setting)
2973  if (mod->op == SPELLMOD_CASTING_TIME && basevalue >= T(10 * IN_MILLISECONDS) && mod->value <= -100)
2974  continue;
2975 
2976  totalpct += mod->value;
2977  }
2978 
2979  if (mod->isFinite && finalUse)
2980  {
2981  bool consume = true;
2982  if (!m_consumedMods) // If empty pointer then immediately consume
2983  {
2984  consumedFiniteMods.push_back(mod); // need to delay in order to not corrupt the list
2985  consume = false;
2986  }
2987  else if (m_consumedMods->find(SpellModifierPair(mod->spellId, mod->modId)) != m_consumedMods->end()) // if already consumed, dont consume again
2988  consume = false;
2989 
2990  if (consume)
2991  {
2992  --mod->charges;
2993  m_consumedMods->insert(SpellModifierPair(mod->spellId, mod->modId));
2994  if (!mod->charges)
2995  mod->charges = -1;
2996  }
2997  }
2998  }
2999 
3000  for (SpellModifier* mod : consumedFiniteMods)
3001  RemoveAuraCharge(mod->spellId);
3002 
3003  if (totalpct < 0)
3004  totalpct = 0;
3005 
3006  if (totalflat != 0 || totalpct != 100)
3007  basevalue = T((basevalue + totalflat) * std::max(0, totalpct) / 100);
3008 }
3009 
3010 
3011 #endif
